1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 11=

4
00:01:38,487 --> 00:01:40,177
Weiwei, you're here.

5
00:01:40,727 --> 00:01:41,566
Sorry

6
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:43,018
for making all of you wait.

7
00:01:44,768 --> 00:01:46,206
Weiwei, this is...

8
00:01:46,207 --> 00:01:47,617
Sorry for being late.

9
00:01:47,688 --> 00:01:48,446
Not at all.

10
00:01:48,447 --> 00:01:50,097
We were just looking around.

11
00:01:53,248 --> 00:01:55,537
"A single man
in possession of good fortune

12
00:01:55,608 --> 00:01:57,457
must be in want of a wife."

13
00:01:57,847 --> 00:01:59,218
I didn't expect it to be you, though.

14
00:02:00,408 --> 00:02:03,058
Jiang is no Mr. Darcy.

15
00:02:05,287 --> 00:02:06,566
Pride and Prejudice

16
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:07,366
is Weiwei's

17
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,737
favorite novel.

18
00:02:08,808 --> 00:02:10,817
I didn't know
you're familiar with it too.

19
00:02:10,888 --> 00:02:11,807
Not at all.

20
00:02:11,808 --> 00:02:13,097
I don't know the story at all.

21
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:14,967
I only remember

22
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:16,218
the first sentence.

23
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:17,697
Me too.

24
00:02:17,968 --> 00:02:18,898
Jiaqiao.

25
00:02:19,088 --> 00:02:21,498
Mrs. Jiang is so much
more interesting than you are.

26
00:02:22,408 --> 00:02:23,218
I...

27
00:02:23,327 --> 00:02:24,726
Excuse me

28
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:26,097
for not attending your wedding

29
00:02:26,128 --> 00:02:28,178
because I was on
a trip with my children.

30
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:30,778
It was a classy wedding, though.

31
00:02:31,447 --> 00:02:32,378
Thank you.

32
00:02:32,847 --> 00:02:33,807
Let's begin.

33
00:02:33,808 --> 00:02:35,058
Very well, this way, please.

34
00:02:53,727 --> 00:02:55,087
I love this.

35
00:02:55,088 --> 00:02:56,417
It suits you.

36
00:03:14,887 --> 00:03:15,738
Weiwei.

37
00:03:15,887 --> 00:03:17,367
We will be exhibiting

38
00:03:17,368 --> 00:03:19,378
this series for the first time globally.

39
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:21,367
Our first stop is Shanghai.

40
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:22,058
Yes.

41
00:03:22,088 --> 00:03:24,297
It's inspired by ancient folklore

42
00:03:24,447 --> 00:03:26,087
of a mysterious goddess

43
00:03:26,088 --> 00:03:27,886
from the forest

44
00:03:27,887 --> 00:03:29,857
clothed in ivy braids.

45
00:03:29,887 --> 00:03:32,046
She held a precious jewel,

46
00:03:32,047 --> 00:03:33,647
and when she threw it up to the sky,

47
00:03:33,648 --> 00:03:35,817
it broke down into millions of stars.

48
00:03:35,928 --> 00:03:36,967
This luminous gem

49
00:03:36,968 --> 00:03:39,058
is our signature piece this time.

50
00:03:41,128 --> 00:03:41,647
What is it?

51
00:03:41,648 --> 00:03:42,647
You knew I've always wanted

52
00:03:42,648 --> 00:03:43,687
to add

53
00:03:43,688 --> 00:03:46,006
a good imperial green
jade necklace to my collection

54
00:03:46,007 --> 00:03:47,817
to pair with my ring.

55
00:03:47,968 --> 00:03:49,726
What do you think?

56
00:03:49,727 --> 00:03:51,097
This is a splendid necklace.

57
00:03:51,208 --> 00:03:52,338
It suits you well.

58
00:03:53,528 --> 00:03:54,286
Does it make me

59
00:03:54,287 --> 00:03:55,817
look older?

60
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:57,537
Of course not, Weiwei.

61
00:03:57,567 --> 00:03:59,537
You're worrying for nothing.

62
00:03:59,968 --> 00:04:00,606
Then, do you think

63
00:04:00,607 --> 00:04:01,738
I should get this set?

64
00:04:01,968 --> 00:04:02,898
It looks wonderful.

65
00:04:03,248 --> 00:04:03,967
Manager,

66
00:04:03,968 --> 00:04:05,127
can you let Weiwei here

67
00:04:05,128 --> 00:04:05,687
try them on?

68
00:04:05,688 --> 00:04:06,857
Of course.

69
00:04:09,847 --> 00:04:11,417
Let me help you.

70
00:04:19,208 --> 00:04:19,977
Mrs. Jiang.

71
00:04:20,007 --> 00:04:21,538
Let me put this on you.

72
00:04:22,248 --> 00:04:24,017
Try it on.

73
00:04:25,407 --> 00:04:26,777
It's beautiful.

74
00:04:28,887 --> 00:04:29,897
You look nice.

75
00:04:30,608 --> 00:04:32,406
My brother has talked to the bank.

76
00:04:32,407 --> 00:04:33,697
About what?

77
00:04:34,087 --> 00:04:34,966
Buy whatever you want.

78
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:36,257
There's no credit limit.

79
00:04:37,128 --> 00:04:38,418
It suits you well.

80
00:04:39,168 --> 00:04:40,687
Everyone thinks that imperial green

81
00:04:40,688 --> 00:04:41,807
is the most expensive kind of jade,

82
00:04:41,808 --> 00:04:42,646
but imperial purple jade

83
00:04:42,647 --> 00:04:43,966
is actually the rarest.

84
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:44,886
Furthermore, purple

85
00:04:44,887 --> 00:04:46,378
is truly a royal color.

86
00:04:46,688 --> 00:04:48,337
Why don't you buy this, Weiwei?

87
00:04:48,407 --> 00:04:50,058
This is the one and only set
there is in this world.

88
00:04:52,207 --> 00:04:53,098
Buy it.

89
00:04:54,007 --> 00:04:55,098
Buy it.

90
00:05:00,168 --> 00:05:01,137
How much for this?

91
00:05:08,447 --> 00:05:09,607
This necklace is priced at

92
00:05:09,608 --> 00:05:10,697
1.2 million.

93
00:05:10,728 --> 00:05:11,657
1.2 million...

94
00:05:12,368 --> 00:05:13,697
Renminbi?

95
00:05:13,887 --> 00:05:14,697
No.

96
00:05:14,808 --> 00:05:16,418
It's 1.2 million US dollars.

97
00:05:17,728 --> 00:05:18,697
Shut up.

98
00:05:18,887 --> 00:05:20,178
Okay, I'll keep quiet.

99
00:05:26,007 --> 00:05:26,646
Miss, you're back.

100
00:05:26,647 --> 00:05:27,446
Where's my brother?

101
00:05:27,447 --> 00:05:28,498
He's resting upstairs.

102
00:05:28,728 --> 00:05:29,607
Miss, are you hungry?

103
00:05:29,608 --> 00:05:30,847
Let me heat up some food for you.

104
00:05:30,848 --> 00:05:32,657
No, I'm too angry to eat.

105
00:05:33,007 --> 00:05:33,646
Ma'am, you're back too.

106
00:05:33,647 --> 00:05:34,886
What a petty

107
00:05:34,887 --> 00:05:36,378
and ignorant woman.

108
00:05:36,728 --> 00:05:38,178
Jiang Jiaqiao, stand right there.

109
00:05:39,407 --> 00:05:40,766
Make yourself clear.

110
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,287
Do you think our family is that poor?

111
00:05:42,288 --> 00:05:43,766
Must you ask about the price

112
00:05:43,767 --> 00:05:45,127
right there and then?

113
00:05:45,128 --> 00:05:46,247
It's normal to inquire prices

114
00:05:46,248 --> 00:05:47,406
when you're shopping.

115
00:05:47,407 --> 00:05:48,927
You haven't been listening

116
00:05:48,928 --> 00:05:50,738
to everything I've said.

117
00:05:50,808 --> 00:05:51,978
Who do you think Weiwei is?

118
00:05:52,928 --> 00:05:54,607
Take a look at
any international luxury store

119
00:05:54,608 --> 00:05:56,047
and their VIP list.

120
00:05:56,048 --> 00:05:57,766
Try finding one without her name on it.

121
00:05:57,767 --> 00:05:58,938
What's it got to do with me?

122
00:05:59,007 --> 00:06:00,098
You...

123
00:06:00,368 --> 00:06:00,886
Wait,

124
00:06:00,887 --> 00:06:02,367
I thought you're supposed to be smart.

125
00:06:02,368 --> 00:06:04,086
You don't understand?

126
00:06:04,087 --> 00:06:05,526
Weiwei looks down on people

127
00:06:05,527 --> 00:06:06,287
who cares about the price

128
00:06:06,288 --> 00:06:07,566
when they go shopping,

129
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:08,326
understand?

130
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:09,897
Do we really need
to put on a facade like that?

131
00:06:12,728 --> 00:06:13,566
My dear brother,

132
00:06:13,567 --> 00:06:15,777
what kind of wife have you gotten?

133
00:06:25,527 --> 00:06:26,457
You're back.

134
00:06:32,688 --> 00:06:33,577
What is it?

135
00:06:34,087 --> 00:06:35,017
You're upset?

136
00:06:36,647 --> 00:06:37,577
Jiang,

137
00:06:37,887 --> 00:06:39,858
Is it true that special people like you

138
00:06:39,887 --> 00:06:40,727
never look at the price

139
00:06:40,728 --> 00:06:42,098
when you go shopping?

140
00:06:43,128 --> 00:06:44,978
What do you mean by special?

141
00:06:45,327 --> 00:06:47,298
Are you really that rich?

142
00:06:48,728 --> 00:06:50,298
What are you trying to say?

143
00:06:50,808 --> 00:06:53,538
You people wouldn't even bat an eye

144
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:55,098
when you spend
a million to buy some jewelry.

145
00:06:56,688 --> 00:06:58,178
A million?

146
00:06:58,647 --> 00:06:59,807
That is a little pricey.

147
00:06:59,808 --> 00:07:01,257
A little?

148
00:07:01,647 --> 00:07:03,406
It's a million,

149
00:07:03,407 --> 00:07:04,938
not a hundred.

150
00:07:05,007 --> 00:07:06,178
I'm talking millions,

151
00:07:06,327 --> 00:07:07,938
and in US dollars.

152
00:07:08,447 --> 00:07:09,817
That's what you don't understand.

153
00:07:10,527 --> 00:07:12,337
We call this an entrance ticket.

154
00:07:13,248 --> 00:07:14,337
What do you mean?

155
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:21,378
A million dollars

156
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:22,526
is also

157
00:07:22,527 --> 00:07:24,098
a large sum of money to me.

158
00:07:26,048 --> 00:07:27,047
But, if you're hanging out

159
00:07:27,048 --> 00:07:28,378
with Xu Weiwei,

160
00:07:28,567 --> 00:07:29,697
you should have bought it.

161
00:07:30,288 --> 00:07:31,498
If you don't,

162
00:07:32,207 --> 00:07:33,697
she'd assume that you can't afford it,

163
00:07:34,887 --> 00:07:36,017
which also implies

164
00:07:36,327 --> 00:07:37,858
that I can't afford it too.

165
00:07:39,527 --> 00:07:40,167
I'm in the middle

166
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,897
of an investment deal with her husband.

167
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:43,418
Now, if I can't afford it,
what else would it imply?

168
00:07:44,288 --> 00:07:45,777
It means I don't have
the financial capability.

169
00:07:46,608 --> 00:07:47,257
That's what

170
00:07:47,288 --> 00:07:49,418
the entrance ticket means.

171
00:07:51,248 --> 00:07:51,966
I don't understand.

172
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:54,217
That just sounds like
a ridiculously expensive ticket.

173
00:07:54,288 --> 00:07:55,047
Right now,

174
00:07:55,048 --> 00:07:56,897
you're not just representing yourself,

175
00:07:57,248 --> 00:07:58,697
but also me.

176
00:08:00,128 --> 00:08:01,098
Mrs. Jiang,

177
00:08:01,207 --> 00:08:02,657
you need to take part

178
00:08:03,048 --> 00:08:04,418
in this performance as well.

179
00:08:06,207 --> 00:08:08,058
Come on, don't be angry.

180
00:08:08,447 --> 00:08:10,137
Xu Weiwei's
birthday party is in two days.

181
00:08:10,447 --> 00:08:11,086
You should bring

182
00:08:11,087 --> 00:08:12,697
something valuable as a ticket.

183
00:08:13,207 --> 00:08:14,498
But, Jiang.

184
00:08:14,887 --> 00:08:16,287
Wearing such an

185
00:08:16,288 --> 00:08:17,577
expensive necklace

186
00:08:17,608 --> 00:08:19,367
would really stress me out.

187
00:08:19,368 --> 00:08:21,127
Just its weight alone
is enough to petrify me.

188
00:08:21,128 --> 00:08:22,006
My neck would be

189
00:08:22,007 --> 00:08:23,337
frozen in place.

190
00:08:25,128 --> 00:08:25,807
Thank you for your hard work,

191
00:08:25,808 --> 00:08:26,538
Mrs. Jiang.

192
00:08:26,848 --> 00:08:27,487
Here,

193
00:08:27,488 --> 00:08:29,017
I'm at your service.

194
00:08:31,288 --> 00:08:32,406
But, I really don't like

195
00:08:32,407 --> 00:08:34,897
going to such events.

196
00:08:35,007 --> 00:08:36,217
I know, I know.

197
00:08:37,087 --> 00:08:38,338
Please do it for me.

198
00:08:45,287 --> 00:08:46,487
Push harder, here.

199
00:08:46,488 --> 00:08:47,218
Okay.

200
00:08:48,047 --> 00:08:50,006
Well, are you happy with my service?

201
00:08:50,007 --> 00:08:51,057
I guess it's okay.

202
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:53,730
(Daming Smart Home)

203
00:09:07,568 --> 00:09:09,046
(Mom: When are you coming home?)

204
00:09:09,047 --> 00:09:09,806
(You weren't back last week,)

205
00:09:09,807 --> 00:09:11,257
(and your dad is upset.)

206
00:09:11,368 --> 00:09:12,937
(Remember to talk to him.)

207
00:09:14,088 --> 00:09:15,286
(Xiang Qian:
We didn't go home last week,)

208
00:09:15,287 --> 00:09:16,537
(and the old guy is mad.)

209
00:09:16,608 --> 00:09:18,218
(We have to go home this weekend.)

210
00:09:24,407 --> 00:09:25,978
(Xiang Nan: Forced socialization.)

211
00:09:26,047 --> 00:09:27,057
(How exhausting.)

212
00:09:32,448 --> 00:09:33,567
(Xiang Qian: Saturday or Sunday?)

213
00:09:33,568 --> 00:09:34,487
(You guys choose first.)

214
00:09:34,488 --> 00:09:35,698
(No skipping this time.)

215
00:09:45,488 --> 00:09:46,338
Here.

216
00:09:46,568 --> 00:09:47,378
Try this.

217
00:09:47,887 --> 00:09:50,137
You girls are always so busy.

218
00:09:50,448 --> 00:09:51,886
I'm so excited

219
00:09:51,887 --> 00:09:52,567
to see you home.

220
00:09:52,568 --> 00:09:53,378
Thank you, Dad.

221
00:09:53,527 --> 00:09:54,926
I simply whipped up some quick dishes.

222
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:56,607
"Simply"?

223
00:09:56,608 --> 00:09:57,367
I thought

224
00:09:57,368 --> 00:09:59,006
a Michelin-starred chef came over

225
00:09:59,007 --> 00:10:00,087
to cook for us.

226
00:10:00,088 --> 00:10:01,367
Your cooking has really

227
00:10:01,368 --> 00:10:02,207
improved a lot.

228
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:03,498
It's delicious.

229
00:10:03,927 --> 00:10:05,646
The ribs are fantastic.

230
00:10:05,647 --> 00:10:06,886
You knew we're on a diet,

231
00:10:06,887 --> 00:10:08,458
and that sugar is just on spot.

232
00:10:09,088 --> 00:10:10,006
You must have been

233
00:10:10,007 --> 00:10:11,098
really famished

234
00:10:11,368 --> 00:10:13,297
out there, haven't you?

235
00:10:13,687 --> 00:10:14,967
They're just flattering you.

236
00:10:14,968 --> 00:10:16,937
Are you really taking it seriously?

237
00:10:17,088 --> 00:10:18,406
Your mother can be a wet blanket.

238
00:10:18,407 --> 00:10:19,297
Yes, you.

239
00:10:19,448 --> 00:10:20,487
It does taste good.

240
00:10:20,488 --> 00:10:21,766
It does.

241
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:22,498
Dad,

242
00:10:22,608 --> 00:10:24,578
even when there's no one visiting,

243
00:10:24,728 --> 00:10:26,327
you can serve your signature dishes

244
00:10:26,328 --> 00:10:27,858
like wine chicken,

245
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:29,286
drunken prawns, and drunken crabs,

246
00:10:29,287 --> 00:10:30,567
can't you?

247
00:10:30,568 --> 00:10:31,458
Agreed.

248
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:33,257
Of course.

249
00:10:33,608 --> 00:10:34,526
If you'd come back home,

250
00:10:34,527 --> 00:10:35,618
I'll cook them every day.

251
00:10:36,128 --> 00:10:37,447
I don't see them today, though.

252
00:10:37,448 --> 00:10:38,406
I can't see them.

253
00:10:38,407 --> 00:10:38,686
I can't see them.

254
00:10:38,687 --> 00:10:39,526
I haven't had any.

255
00:10:39,527 --> 00:10:40,006
Where are they?

256
00:10:40,007 --> 00:10:41,177
The crabs are not drunk yet.

257
00:10:42,128 --> 00:10:43,657
They're still drinking.

258
00:10:47,248 --> 00:10:48,207
Dad, listen.

259
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:49,978
Don't hang out with Gu too often

260
00:10:50,007 --> 00:10:50,967
and blabber too much.

261
00:10:50,968 --> 00:10:52,286
He loves collecting gossip

262
00:10:52,287 --> 00:10:54,046
and spreading them everywhere.

263
00:10:54,047 --> 00:10:54,646
Yeah.

264
00:10:54,647 --> 00:10:56,487
Mom is good at knitting.

265
00:10:56,488 --> 00:10:58,367
You should learn how to knit from her.

266
00:10:58,368 --> 00:10:59,526
You want me to learn how to knit?

267
00:10:59,527 --> 00:10:59,847
Yeah.

268
00:10:59,848 --> 00:11:00,806
That's what Xiang Zhong said, too.

269
00:11:00,807 --> 00:11:02,897
He said knitting can prevent dementia.

270
00:11:03,007 --> 00:11:04,978
He also said that

271
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,567
it can prevent

272
00:11:07,568 --> 00:11:08,417
some disease called

273
00:11:08,448 --> 00:11:10,458
"meddling around
other people's business".

274
00:11:10,728 --> 00:11:12,127
That's an important benefit.

275
00:11:12,128 --> 00:11:13,417
Who's meddling around?

276
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,257
Listen,

277
00:11:15,368 --> 00:11:17,698
just come home often, will you?

278
00:11:18,047 --> 00:11:19,526
When we get to see you,

279
00:11:19,527 --> 00:11:21,137
we'd stay happy every day,

280
00:11:21,448 --> 00:11:23,297
and we'd be free of dementia.

281
00:11:23,488 --> 00:11:24,458
Understood?

282
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,338
My mother wouldn't get dementia.

283
00:11:26,407 --> 00:11:27,686
You don't have to worry, Mom.

284
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:28,858
Only me, then?

285
00:11:29,128 --> 00:11:30,177
That's hard to say.

286
00:11:30,328 --> 00:11:31,858
If you keep hanging out with Gu,

287
00:11:31,887 --> 00:11:33,057
that'd be a bad idea.

288
00:11:33,248 --> 00:11:34,286
You'd be limiting
your mind to trivial matters.

289
00:11:34,287 --> 00:11:35,607
Wait, whose phone is that?

290
00:11:35,608 --> 00:11:36,618
Mine.

