00:24:41,568 --> 00:24:43,298
I'm just so worried about her.

585
00:25:00,967 --> 00:25:02,807
This tastes awful.

586
00:25:02,808 --> 00:25:03,618
What's wrong?

587
00:25:07,967 --> 00:25:09,686
I thought I added soy sauce.

588
00:25:09,687 --> 00:25:11,007
It's okay, leave it here.

589
00:25:11,008 --> 00:25:11,847
I'll cook another one.

590
00:25:11,848 --> 00:25:12,926
Forget it, we don't have time.

591
00:25:12,927 --> 00:25:13,818
Let's eat something else.

592
00:25:14,407 --> 00:25:15,417
Porridge will be ready soon.

593
00:25:17,328 --> 00:25:18,578
Oh my.

594
00:25:22,768 --> 00:25:25,287
Qi "spelled" her milk.

595
00:25:25,288 --> 00:25:26,258
Let me help you.

596
00:25:27,727 --> 00:25:28,977
My...

597
00:25:29,407 --> 00:25:30,047
Mom,

598
00:25:30,048 --> 00:25:32,937
I "spelled" my milk too.

599
00:25:33,128 --> 00:25:34,378
Both of you...

600
00:25:35,927 --> 00:25:37,047
It's not "spelled".

601
00:25:37,048 --> 00:25:37,886
It's "spilled".

602
00:25:37,887 --> 00:25:38,646
I'll get the door.

603
00:25:38,647 --> 00:25:40,137
"Spelled".

604
00:25:40,368 --> 00:25:41,166
"Spilled".

605
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:42,926
"Spill"...

606
00:25:42,927 --> 00:25:44,417
Mom, what brings you here?

607
00:25:45,207 --> 00:25:46,897
Don't even mention it.

608
00:25:47,008 --> 00:25:47,807
"Spelled".

609
00:25:47,808 --> 00:25:48,646
"Spelled".

610
00:25:48,647 --> 00:25:49,246
Eat your breakfast.

611
00:25:49,247 --> 00:25:50,246
"Spelled".

612
00:25:50,247 --> 00:25:51,098
What are they doing?

613
00:25:51,407 --> 00:25:51,886
Quiet.

614
00:25:51,887 --> 00:25:52,618
The usual antics.

615
00:25:55,088 --> 00:25:55,527
Mom,

616
00:25:55,528 --> 00:25:56,858
what brings you here so early?

617
00:25:56,927 --> 00:25:57,567
Don't even mention it.

618
00:25:57,568 --> 00:25:58,646
I was supposed to meet

619
00:25:58,647 --> 00:25:59,926
my friends for shopping,

620
00:25:59,927 --> 00:26:01,406
but I misread the time

621
00:26:01,407 --> 00:26:03,127
and left home an hour early.

622
00:26:03,128 --> 00:26:04,457
What's going on here?

623
00:26:05,288 --> 00:26:06,338
Where's Zhang?

624
00:26:07,328 --> 00:26:08,217
She quit.

625
00:26:08,247 --> 00:26:10,338
She had to go home, so she quit.

626
00:26:11,407 --> 00:26:13,298
That sounds troublesome.

627
00:26:13,328 --> 00:26:14,807
Let me call my friends

628
00:26:14,808 --> 00:26:15,446
to tell them I'm not joining.

629
00:26:15,447 --> 00:26:16,367
I'll stay here and help.

630
00:26:16,368 --> 00:26:17,206
No.

631
00:26:17,207 --> 00:26:18,446
Just go.

632
00:26:18,447 --> 00:26:19,686
Tell them you'll join later.

633
00:26:19,687 --> 00:26:20,367
Help me send the kids

634
00:26:20,368 --> 00:26:20,767
to school.

635
00:26:20,768 --> 00:26:22,137
But you don't have a nanny now.

636
00:26:22,487 --> 00:26:24,127
We'll find another one soon.

637
00:26:24,128 --> 00:26:25,417
We'll find an agency.

638
00:26:27,407 --> 00:26:28,206
You don't need me here?

639
00:26:28,207 --> 00:26:28,567
No.

640
00:26:28,568 --> 00:26:29,726
Just take them to school

641
00:26:29,727 --> 00:26:30,246
after this.

642
00:26:30,247 --> 00:26:31,206
I'm taking them to school,

643
00:26:31,207 --> 00:26:31,646
right?

644
00:26:31,647 --> 00:26:33,166
Okay, pack everything they need

645
00:26:33,167 --> 00:26:34,737
in school later.

646
00:26:34,967 --> 00:26:35,977
Their bags.

647
00:26:36,647 --> 00:26:37,897
Eat up.

648
00:26:38,487 --> 00:26:40,338
Bai, eat up.

649
00:26:41,247 --> 00:26:41,966
What's wrong?

650
00:26:41,967 --> 00:26:43,486
I haven't seen you for days.

651
00:26:43,487 --> 00:26:44,897
Are you feeling unwell?

652
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:47,098
You seem tired.

653
00:26:53,808 --> 00:26:55,298
You don't feel like eating?

654
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:57,018
You should eat something.

655
00:26:58,808 --> 00:26:59,657
Bai.

656
00:27:06,568 --> 00:27:08,098
It's here to say goodbye.

657
00:27:11,447 --> 00:27:13,137
I came here a few days ago to feed it,

658
00:27:13,288 --> 00:27:14,417
and I didn't see it.

659
00:27:15,247 --> 00:27:16,737
Why did you say so?

660
00:27:19,088 --> 00:27:20,166
Cats can usually sense it

661
00:27:20,167 --> 00:27:21,417
when they're about to die.

662
00:27:21,687 --> 00:27:23,417
It knew its days are almost over,

663
00:27:23,727 --> 00:27:25,258
so it came back to see you one last time

664
00:27:25,647 --> 00:27:26,686
before finding

665
00:27:26,687 --> 00:27:28,018
a quiet spot to leave.

666
00:27:29,887 --> 00:27:31,338
Don't be too sad.

667
00:27:32,647 --> 00:27:33,977
You were so nice to it.

668
00:27:34,247 --> 00:27:35,697
It will remember you.

669
00:27:44,368 --> 00:27:45,246
Next time, you can use my bowl

670
00:27:45,247 --> 00:27:46,578
to feed the cats.

671
00:27:47,008 --> 00:27:48,737
It's more convenient and less wasteful.

672
00:27:51,048 --> 00:27:52,018
This is my home.

673
00:27:52,368 --> 00:27:53,246
You live here?

674
00:27:53,247 --> 00:27:54,657
Yes, this is my backyard.

675
00:27:55,368 --> 00:27:56,417
What a coincidence.

676
00:27:56,487 --> 00:27:57,327
I'm staying on the second floor

677
00:27:57,328 --> 00:27:58,618
right across the street.

678
00:28:00,568 --> 00:28:01,897
That is a coincidence.

679
00:28:03,167 --> 00:28:04,258
I'm going home, then.

680
00:28:04,608 --> 00:28:05,047
Bye.

681
00:28:05,048 --> 00:28:05,737
Bye.

682
00:28:17,608 --> 00:28:18,977
Okay, thank you.

683
00:28:19,328 --> 00:28:20,177
Goodbye.

684
00:28:26,288 --> 00:28:27,538
What did the police say?

685
00:28:30,848 --> 00:28:31,847
When the police

686
00:28:31,848 --> 00:28:33,137
found them yesterday,

687
00:28:33,608 --> 00:28:34,406
the kids did ask her

688
00:28:34,407 --> 00:28:36,007
to buy some cream puffs,

689
00:28:36,008 --> 00:28:37,778
and Zhang Hui bought some for them

690
00:28:38,008 --> 00:28:39,567
before heading to

691
00:28:39,568 --> 00:28:40,206
the learning center,

692
00:28:40,207 --> 00:28:41,778
but they lost their way.

693
00:28:42,247 --> 00:28:43,137
However,

694
00:28:43,887 --> 00:28:45,697
the police has also found out

695
00:28:45,967 --> 00:28:47,007
that Zhang Hui's husband

696
00:28:47,008 --> 00:28:48,538
has racked up a lot of debts.

697
00:28:49,088 --> 00:28:50,937
Was she intending to steal our kids?

698
00:28:52,447 --> 00:28:53,406
We don't know for sure.

699
00:28:53,407 --> 00:28:54,858
Of course she wouldn't admit it.

700
00:28:56,887 --> 00:28:57,646
We simply cannot

701
00:28:57,647 --> 00:28:58,937
hire her anymore.

702
00:29:01,088 --> 00:29:02,697
Yes, we can't.

703
00:29:06,088 --> 00:29:07,137
What is this?

704
00:29:08,207 --> 00:29:10,417
So, are you going to tell your parents?

705
00:29:11,528 --> 00:29:12,807
It was

706
00:29:12,808 --> 00:29:14,018
a false alarm,

707
00:29:14,687 --> 00:29:15,897
so let's not tell them.

708
00:29:19,207 --> 00:29:19,767
Wait.

709
00:29:19,768 --> 00:29:21,937
You can't keep it a secret forever.

710
00:29:22,727 --> 00:29:24,486
Your mom just came over and saw

711
00:29:24,487 --> 00:29:25,657
how messy things were.

712
00:29:26,568 --> 00:29:27,646
What if

713
00:29:27,647 --> 00:29:28,977
the kids blurt it out

714
00:29:29,288 --> 00:29:31,298
before the new nanny arrives?

715
00:29:32,887 --> 00:29:34,258
How do we even look for a new nanny now?

716
00:29:36,808 --> 00:29:38,007
Every nanny I see

717
00:29:38,008 --> 00:29:39,818
looks like a human trafficker now.

718
00:29:50,848 --> 00:29:52,538
My youngest aunt

719
00:29:53,167 --> 00:29:54,246
called me lately

720
00:29:54,247 --> 00:29:56,417
and said she's got a lot of free time.

721
00:29:56,808 --> 00:29:58,166
If we need any help,

722
00:29:58,167 --> 00:29:59,087
she could come over

723
00:29:59,088 --> 00:30:00,457
and help out.

724
00:30:02,528 --> 00:30:04,367
My aunt is part

725
00:30:04,368 --> 00:30:05,807
of our family, right?

726
00:30:05,808 --> 00:30:08,217
It's better than
getting someone outside.

727
00:30:08,487 --> 00:30:09,697
Of course.

728
00:30:10,528 --> 00:30:11,618
But

729
00:30:12,048 --> 00:30:13,697
she's your aunt.

730
00:30:13,927 --> 00:30:15,977
Do you think it's appropriate for her

731
00:30:16,528 --> 00:30:17,778
to be our nanny?

732
00:30:20,167 --> 00:30:22,166
When I asked her, she said

733
00:30:22,167 --> 00:30:23,417
she's fine with it,

734
00:30:23,487 --> 00:30:24,737
and it depends on you.

735
00:30:27,768 --> 00:30:28,657
What do you think?

736
00:30:31,447 --> 00:30:32,457
I...

737
00:30:39,167 --> 00:30:41,977
I don't really have any thoughts.

738
00:30:43,247 --> 00:30:44,897
I won't insist on it, either.

739
00:30:46,487 --> 00:30:47,778
You call the shots.

740
00:30:58,247 --> 00:30:59,497
Let me think about it.

741
00:31:01,608 --> 00:31:02,618
Go ahead.

742
00:31:18,528 --> 00:31:20,726
Is this dead cat supposed
to be in the garbage dump?

743
00:31:20,727 --> 00:31:22,047
I guess it's not considered

744
00:31:22,048 --> 00:31:23,246
kitchen waste,

745
00:31:23,247 --> 00:31:24,657
but it's not recyclable either.

746
00:31:24,727 --> 00:31:26,457
Put it in the others section, then.

747
00:31:26,647 --> 00:31:27,567
What if it rots?

748
00:31:27,568 --> 00:31:28,618
It'd stink.

749
00:31:28,647 --> 00:31:29,697
Or hazardous waste?

750
00:31:30,088 --> 00:31:31,527
What should we do?

751
00:31:31,528 --> 00:31:32,497
I'll handle it.

752
00:31:33,167 --> 00:31:35,098
Thank you, young man.

753
00:31:35,288 --> 00:31:36,137
Let's go.

754
00:31:39,167 --> 00:31:40,298
Poor cat.

755
00:31:41,008 --> 00:31:42,378
How are you going to handle it?

756
00:31:42,727 --> 00:31:44,177
I'll take it to a pet cremation center.

757
00:31:45,727 --> 00:31:47,177
It came to say goodbye to us,

758
00:31:48,407 --> 00:31:49,858
so we should repay it with kindness.

759
00:31:51,128 --> 00:31:52,858
Sure, I'll search online.

760
00:31:53,608 --> 00:31:54,926
I guess most taxis won't be happy

761
00:31:54,927 --> 00:31:56,567
carrying a dead cat in their car.

762
00:31:56,568 --> 00:31:57,217
Yeah.

763
00:31:58,568 --> 00:31:59,578
Do you have a car?

764
00:32:01,887 --> 00:32:03,497
Yes, but I'm not a good driver.

765
00:32:04,008 --> 00:32:05,098
I'll drive.

766
00:32:10,447 --> 00:32:11,977
Just continue straight.

767
00:32:16,447 --> 00:32:17,087
I haven't seen you

768
00:32:17,088 --> 00:32:18,457
around the neighborhood before.

769
00:32:21,088 --> 00:32:22,778
I'm just house-sitting for my cousin

770
00:32:23,848 --> 00:32:26,098
while taking care of his cats.

771
00:32:26,647 --> 00:32:28,378
How many cats does he have?

772
00:32:28,927 --> 00:32:29,977
Three.

773
00:32:41,288 --> 00:32:42,378
Why?

774
00:32:43,447 --> 00:32:44,618
Sorry,

775
00:32:45,048 --> 00:32:46,618
but the air here kind of stinks.

776
00:32:52,247 --> 00:32:53,047
I should be the one apologizing.

777
00:32:53,048 --> 00:32:54,446
This is my ex-husband's car.

778
00:32:54,447 --> 00:32:55,646
He's not very particular

779
00:32:55,647 --> 00:32:56,367
about hygiene.

780
00:32:56,368 --> 00:32:57,646
That's why it's so dirty and messy.

781
00:32:57,647 --> 00:32:58,937
I rarely use this car, too.

782
00:33:01,167 --> 00:33:02,338
I'm a bit of a clean freak.

783
00:33:03,207 --> 00:33:04,298
Sorry about that.

784
00:33:25,407 --> 00:33:26,486
I guess you'll have to make do

785
00:33:26,487 --> 00:33:27,897
with this tissue here.

786
00:33:28,568 --> 00:33:29,897
Thank you.

787
00:33:41,407 --> 00:33:42,457
You're divorced?

788
00:33:44,167 --> 00:33:45,618
Still in the cooling off period.

789
00:33:49,447 --> 00:33:50,818
I just broke up with my girlfriend.

790
00:33:55,167 --> 00:33:56,457
I'm Wang Yuxi.

791
00:33:57,887 --> 00:33:58,977
I'm Xiang Zhong.

792
00:34:50,287 --> 00:34:51,258
Let's go.

793
00:34:57,888 --> 00:34:59,457
Have you ever had any pets?

794
00:35:00,528 --> 00:35:01,577
No.

795
00:35:02,488 --> 00:35:03,778
When I was a kid,

796
00:35:03,847 --> 00:35:05,258
I used to have a miniature pinscher,

797
00:35:06,528 --> 00:35:08,338
but it was born with heart disease,

798
00:35:09,568 --> 00:35:11,457
and it succumbed to a heart attack.

799
00:35:11,847 --> 00:35:12,858
Then,

800
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:15,206
I kept a cat in Shanghai

801
00:35:15,207 --> 00:35:16,487
with my girlfriend.

802
00:35:16,488 --> 00:35:18,298
We took care of it together.

803
00:35:19,608 --> 00:35:20,286
After we broke up,

804
00:35:20,287 --> 00:35:21,738
she left me the cat.

805
00:35:25,488 --> 00:35:27,378
The cat later caught an infection

806
00:35:28,167 --> 00:35:29,537
and died.

807
00:35:31,088 --> 00:35:32,218
I guess

808
00:35:34,448 --> 00:35:37,097
you're not suited to keep pets.

809
00:35:41,128 --> 00:35:42,658
Was your cat

810
00:35:43,568 --> 00:35:44,806
buried here

811
00:35:44,807 --> 00:35:46,698
like the cat earlier?

812
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:50,206
I brought its ashes with me

813
00:35:50,207 --> 00:35:51,378
and traveled around.

814
00:35:52,408 --> 00:35:53,897
We visited many places

815
00:35:55,088 --> 00:35:56,457
and stopped in Hainan in the end.

816
00:35:58,088 --> 00:36:00,017
Why Hainan?

817
00:36:09,327 --> 00:36:10,338
My ex.

818
00:36:14,568 --> 00:36:15,527
Last month,
she went back to the Northeast

819
00:36:15,528 --> 00:36:16,698
and got married.

820
00:36:17,767 --> 00:36:20,017
Are you from the Northeast, too?

821
00:36:20,847 --> 00:36:21,897
I'm from Changchun.

822
00:36:21,968 --> 00:36:23,778
I went to college in Changchun.

823
00:36:24,367 --> 00:36:25,537
What a coincidence.

824
00:36:26,528 --> 00:36:27,326
Still,

825
00:36:27,327 --> 00:36:29,138
I'd always wanted to leave that place.

826
00:36:29,488 --> 00:36:31,178
It's too cold in winter.

827
00:36:33,847 --> 00:36:35,617
I've always wanted to leave here.

828
00:36:42,608 --> 00:36:43,698
But in the end,

829
00:36:43,727 --> 00:36:45,097
we happened to meet here.

830
00:36:48,496 --> 00:36:51,447
♪In ordinary times♪

831
00:36:51,697 --> 00:36:53,947
♪I met you♪

832
00:36:55,691 --> 00:36:58,389
♪I don't like fancy stuff♪

833
00:36:58,739 --> 00:37:01,962
♪I only like simple things♪

834
00:37:01,963 --> 00:37:03,646
♪Even time changes♪

835
00:37:03,647 --> 00:37:04,537
Xiang Zhong.

836
00:37:05,077 --> 00:37:07,610
♪Tossing and turning♪

837
00:37:07,647 --> 00:37:08,778
What is it?

838
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:12,005
♪As moments come and go♪

839
00:37:12,450 --> 00:37:15,777
♪More time has passed♪

840
00:37:15,892 --> 00:37:18,871
♪In ordinary times♪

841
00:37:19,215 --> 00:37:21,364
♪I left you♪

842
00:37:23,114 --> 00:37:25,951
♪I forgot some moments♪

843
00:37:26,202 --> 00:37:29,494
♪Some incidents, some promises♪

844
00:37:29,978 --> 00:37:32,542
♪Serendipity is hard to unravel♪

845
00:37:32,543 --> 00:37:36,410
♪All that goes by have changed♪

846
00:37:36,827 --> 00:37:39,231
♪All my longing♪

847
00:37:40,229 --> 00:37:42,860
♪They have not been answered♪

848
00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:45,256
♪Still waiting for your reply♪

849
00:37:45,257 --> 00:37:48,781
♪You and I can skip the small talk♪

850
00:37:48,782 --> 00:37:51,365
♪And keep things ordinary♪

851
00:37:51,756 --> 00:37:54,619
♪Let the sadness wear off♪

852
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:58,934
♪And avoid some of the hassle♪

853
00:37:59,011 --> 00:38:02,108
♪You and I can still salvage♪

854
00:38:02,109 --> 00:38:05,390
♪The ordinary things in our heart♪

855
00:38:05,541 --> 00:38:08,797
♪Just so it mends
some of the heartbreak♪

856
00:38:08,798 --> 00:38:11,477
♪And answers our wishes♪

857
00:38:25,727 --> 00:38:27,778
My brother treats you really well.

858
00:38:54,327 --> 00:38:55,338
(Mr. Jiang: Here yet?)

859
00:38:58,287 --> 00:38:59,338
(Xiang Nan: Almost there.)

860
00:39:00,767 --> 00:39:01,818
(Mr. Jiang: Relax.)

861
00:39:15,727 --> 00:39:17,537
Why does it look
like it's going to rain?

862
00:39:19,088 --> 00:39:20,298
How do you know?

863
00:39:21,088 --> 00:39:22,206
When I left this morning,

864
00:39:22,207 --> 00:39:23,047
the humidity level

865
00:39:23,048 --> 00:39:24,246
was already at 80%,

866
00:39:24,247 --> 00:39:25,778
with heavy storm clouds.

867
00:39:27,528 --> 00:39:28,806
Are you working in the TV station

868
00:39:28,807 --> 00:39:30,097
as a weather reporter?

869
00:39:30,807 --> 00:39:32,057
I'm not.

870
00:39:34,448 --> 00:39:36,178
Actually, I love rain.

871
00:39:37,568 --> 00:39:39,057
Especially during spring.

872
00:39:39,968 --> 00:39:41,087
It rains slow and steady,

873
